  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `2.40.1`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Docker(Linux)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nErigon node works as expected and takes params from docker-compose.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nErigon stopped taking params from docker-compose.\r\nfor example, “--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0”,`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nUpdate Erigon node to version 2.40.1\r\nUpdate Lighthouse to version 3.5.1\r\n\r\nIndicate in docker-compose in command block the following params:\r\n      - --authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n      - --authrpc.port=8551\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nVersion 2.40.1\r\n````\r\n[INFO] [03-17|10:36:49.411] HTTP endpoint opened for Engine API      url=127.0.0.1:8551 ws=true ws.compression=true\r\n[INFO] [03-17|10:36:49.412] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=127.0.0.1:8545 ws=false ws.compression=true grpc=false\r\n\r\n````\r\nVersion 2.39.0\r\n```\r\n{“lvl”:“info”,“msg”:“HTTP endpoint opened for Engine API”,“t”:“2023-03-17T11:06:55.074551379Z”,“url”:“0.0.0.0:8551\",“ws”:true,“ws.compression”:true}\r\n```\r\nSo even after indicating `--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0` param in docker-compose - version 2.40.1 doesn't take it.\r\nVersion 2.39.0 works as expected",
